        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4515,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "As the European Commission seeks to modernise consumer protection through the Digital Fairness Act (DFA), it is vital that the new framework remains innovation-friendly and proportionate, particularly for startups and scaleups that drive Europe’s digital economy.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s0",
          "section_path": [],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 37,
          "char_len": 263
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p16",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4566,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "In Bulgaria, startups and scaleups are among the fastest-growing contributors to innovation, employment, and regional competitiveness. These companies operate under tight resource constraints and already face multiple layers of EU regulation - from the GDPR, DSA, DMA, and AI Act, to existing consumer protection directives. Adding another complex legislative act risks regulatory overlap, legal uncertainty, and compliance fatigue for smaller innovators.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s0",
          "section_path": [],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 60,
          "char_len": 455
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p17",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Enforcement",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "effective enforcement"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "topic": "Harmonisation Across Member States",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "harmonisation across Member States."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 26551,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "While we fully support the EU’s objective of enhancing consumer trust and fairness online, we urge the Commission to prioritise simplification over duplication. Existing legislation - such as the Consumer Rights Directive, Unfair Commercial Practices Directive (UCPD), and Unfair Contract Terms Directive - already provides a strong foundation for consumer protection. Instead of introducing new layers of rules, efforts should focus on effective enforcement and harmonisation across Member States.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s0",
          "section_path": [],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 68,
          "char_len": 498
        }
      },
      {
